@Izzy187  
There is nothing in the wording of [Rooftop Storm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rooftop Storm) that necessitates casting from your hand. It is indeed very plausible to cast and recast [Gravecrawler](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gravecrawler) from the graveyard for free as many times as you like to make [Grimgrin, Corpse-Born](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grimgrin, Corpse-Born) infinitely powerful.  

As for the card itself, although it being a brand new rare makes it difficult to get my hands on, I'm getting two today and finding two more in the near future for my B/U Zombie deck. Fantastic zombie, makes [Diregraf Ghoul](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Diregraf Ghoul) look very mediocre in comparison. 5/5.

Don't get me wrong, this looks like a fantastic card and I want four of them, but I'm not buying the flavor text.  

Lilliana... I hate to break it to you, but if you want to show up the ghoulcallers this li'l guy isn't going to impress anyone. Did you know someone made [a zombie that can make other zombies](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=262852)?  

@Diachronos How about by making a zombie that can *walk?*

@MisterAction:   
Actually, Gravecrawler could be one of the ultimate examples of high-level necromancy.   
How can you really top a Zombie that *just won't die?!*
